Privacy Policy

Effective Date: February 8, 2025

At Nearsapp, we value the privacy of our users and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our app, a social media platform that connects people based on their location. By using Nearsapp, you agree to the collection and use of your data in accordance with this Privacy Policy.

1. Information We Collect
We collect the following personal information when you use Nearsapp:

Account Information: When you create an account, we collect your email address, name, birthday, phone number, and password.
Location Data: We collect and use your location data to provide location-based features such as finding and viewing posts and users nearby. You can choose a specific location on the map to see relevant posts.
Posts and Communications: We collect the content of posts you make and any messages you send to other users or in groups.
Usage Information: We may collect information about how you use our app, including interaction with other users, the content you view, and your engagement with different features of the app.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use your personal information to:

Create and manage your account.
Provide and improve the functionality of our app.
Display posts and users based on your selected location.
Facilitate communication between users, including one-on-one chats and group conversations.
Send you notifications about important updates or interactions with other users.
Ensure the security and integrity of our app.

3. Location Data
We collect and use your location data to offer personalized experiences, such as showing you posts and users near you. Your real-time location is not shared with other users unless you choose to disclose it in a post or conversation. You can control location sharing by adjusting the app's permissions through your device settings.

4. How We Share Your Information
We may share your information under the following circumstances:

With Other Users: Your name and profile information (excluding email, birthday, and phone number) will be visible to other users. Posts and messages you create will be shared with other users in the selected location.
With Third Parties: We may share your data with third-party service providers who help us operate the app, such as hosting providers and analytics services. These third parties are bound by confidentiality agreements and are only authorized to use your data as necessary to provide services to us.
For Legal Purposes: We may disclose your information to comply with legal obligations, such as responding to a subpoena, court order, or legal process, or to protect our rights and the rights of others.

5. Data Security
We take reasonable steps to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no security measure is completely foolproof, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your data.

6. Your Privacy Choices
Location Settings: You can control whether our app can access your location data through your device's location settings.
Account Information: You can update or delete your account information by visiting your account settings in the app.
Communication Preferences: You can control the notifications you receive by adjusting the appâ€™s notification settings.

7. Children's Privacy
Our app is not intended for individuals under the age of 13. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete that information.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by updating the "Effective Date" at the top of this policy. It is your responsibility to review this Privacy Policy periodically for updates.

9. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at wikosac@gmail.com.
